@damitechh @_joemclean @SassCSS I would put the default HTML tags into a shared global file that effects all tags. Then, if you need to override them, you can do so with:

.form {
      h2 {}
      p {}
}

Really, no need to add additional classes if the tags can be overridden. Global modifiers are great too.

